[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m considering if I can write a Java source file within the same package. The rule says tests should be outside library packages, but maybe a dynamic helper could still be in the test source? It states not to place tests in the same package as the library just for access to package-private methods. I think having a top-level test class outside is necessary, so a helper in the library package probably wouldn’t fit. But generated bytecode in tests isn't a source package.
[thinking] 
